# Discussions — <component> (<version>)

This file is the running thread for the user and Claude to discuss the `<component>` review. Append new entries at the bottom — never rewrite or delete prior entries.

Format each entry as:

```
## <YYYY-MM-DD> — <speaker: User | Claude | Codex>
<content>
```

Use this thread for:

- Questions the user wants to dig deeper into after reading `review.md`.
- Clarifications, corrections, or follow-up traces Claude should add to the review.
- Decisions about scope (e.g. "skip the temporal-workflows angle, we'll cover it under the cross-cutting review").
- A final sign-off entry when the user marks the component complete.

When the user says the component is done ("mark complete", "tick it", "done with this one"), the skill writes the sign-off entry here on their behalf and then flips the checklist entry in `../index.md` from `[~]` to `[x]`. The user does not need to write the entry themselves first — saying "mark complete" is enough.
